commit.message:
Change request URLs to use HTTPS (#1050)

Nomacs used HTTP to request for things like version files for auto
updates. Because the version file contains URL, if the file gets
tempered, the user could end up downloading malicious files. Modify the
URLs used in the code so that requests use HTTPS by default, which
should be safer.

commit.message:
Fix random comparison of images (#1051)

Prior to this result of comparison was random each time, resulting in
undefined behavior with e.g. sort.

Now filepath and random global seed are used to keep the random order
proper.

Fixes #953.

commit.message:
Use Exiv2::CommentValue to format Exif.Photo.UserComment metadatum (#1049)

Converting the UserComment exif metadatum to string will result in its
direct/quasi-internal string representation of libexiv2, which may
include a "charset=..." prefix with the charset of the value.

Since we want the actual content/value of UserComment, and the
Exiv2::Value held by Exiv2::Exifdatum is Exiv2::CommentValue, then
cast it to call comment(). The result is converted to QString using
QString::fromStdString(), which converts std::string as UTF-8 string.

For further details, see also the exiv2 ticket:
https://github.com/Exiv2/exiv2/issues/1258

Signed-off-by: Pino Toscano <toscano.pino@tiscali.it>

commit.message:
Replace qt5-default package in Ubuntu

Because Ubuntu dropped the `qt5-default` package in 21.04, the build
instructions will fail. Update the command to use `qtbase5-dev`, which
is a dependency of `qt5-default` instead.

Fixes https://github.com/nomacs/nomacs/issues/1024.
Increase build number
Install Required System Libraries in MSVC build

Include the revision string in about nomacs

The NOMACS_GIT_TAG was defined but not referenced anywhere. Add a new
line in the version info of the about splash screen to display the
updated revision string, which contains the commit hash, the commit
date, and whether the source has modifications that have not been
committed when building. This could be helpful for reporting bugs.

Update Git revision tagging

Building Nomacs from the zip source archives
downloaded from Github fails because the `versionupdate.py` script
calls Git command, which assumes the working direction is a child of
a Git repo.

Move the revision tag logic to the CMake script. Check for the existence
of a `.git` directory to fix the issue.

Also, include the commit date and check whether there are modified files
in the repository. These could be useful when reporting and searching
for bugs. Assemble the result into a constant string for use.

Fixes https://github.com/nomacs/nomacs/issues/1034.

Update group contact info

Add the address to the Matrix chat room. Update the contact info
in the code of conduct to the chat room because the email no longer
exists.

Closes https://github.com/nomacs/nomacs/issues/1027.
Use Visual Studio 2022 to build nomacs now on Windows
Increase build number
Update nomacs.ts
Run clang-format

Remove excessive QT_VERSION guard

Signed-off-by: Vyacheslav Tyrtov <v.tyrtov@gmail.com>

Make cmake scripts Qt6 compliant

CMake now is looking for any available Qt (with preference to Qt6)

To explicitly enable Qt5 build define:
    QT_VERSION_MAJOR=5

Signed-off-by: Vyacheslav Tyrtov <v.tyrtov@gmail.com>

Fix enterEvent backward incompatibility Qt6 -> Qt5

In Qt6 QWidget::enterEvent() signature was changed
https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/widgets-changes-qt6.html#the-qwidget-class

Let's make the code compatible with both Qt5 and Qt6

Signed-off-by: Vyacheslav Tyrtov <v.tyrtov@gmail.com>

Make QtConcurrent::run call Qt version agnostic

In Qt6 the signature of QtConcurrent::run() was changed
https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/concurrent-changes-qt6.html

Let's use lambdas to make the calls version agnostic

This also removes deprecated QWheelEvent::orientation()

There is no

so fix to call the proper version instead:
